Gangaur is a vibrant, 18-day festival primarily celebrated in Rajasthan, India, honoring the union of Lord Shiva (Gan) and Goddess Parvati (Gauri) and symbolizing marital bliss, spring, and harvest. 
The name “Gangaur” is derived from “Gan” (Shiva) and “Gauri” (Parvati), signifying the worship of both deities.
